                            <comment id="12982430" author="srowen" created="Sun, 16 Jan 2011 23:50:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes the code is definitely always interpreting the input as local. So it&apos;s doing what it&apos;s supposed to do for now &amp;#8211; but doesn&apos;t mean it couldn&apos;t do something else. I don&apos;t know this file well. Isabel you touched SequenceFilesFromDirectory recently: do you have thoughts?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12984355" author="smtakeda" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2011 19:45:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi, I came across the need of HDFS support in Sequence Files from Directory, and I made up a patch to get my job done with a simple test case.&lt;br/&gt;
I ran &quot;mvn clean install&quot; on both Mac OS X 10.6.6 and RHL2.6.18-162.2.1.el5.&lt;br/&gt;
Hope I&apos;m on the right track.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12984356" author="smtakeda" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2011 19:46:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch attached.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12984471" author="srowen" created="Thu, 20 Jan 2011 23:37:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There are some minor issues with the style and formatting, but I&apos;ve addressed them locally. I committed with these changes. It seems fine as the change is essentially to replace File with Path for input, to allow for support of local or HDFS files.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12984537" author="hudson" created="Fri, 21 Jan 2011 02:45:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Mahout-Quality #575 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/575/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://hudson.apache.org/hudson/job/Mahout-Quality/575/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MAHOUT-535&quot; title=&quot;mahout seqdirectory reads only from the local filesystem, even when running over Hadoop&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;MAHOUT-535&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;MAHOUT-535&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; Operates now in terms of Path, so it can support local or HDFS file as input&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
